examples.en: They attacked the enemy's line.
They sabotaged the enemy's oil fields.
They attacked the enemy's right flank.
We must strike the enemy's oil fields.
He assassinated his enemy's character.
Our boffins finally broke the enemy's code!
He passed his sword through his enemy's body.
The bridge was enfiladed by the enemy's cannon.
The soldiers could not impede the enemy's advance.
They did a reconnaissance of the enemy's position.
They directed the attacks against the enemy's seaports.
A clever move on our part rolled up the enemy's weak side.
He peered out, trying to get a fix on the enemy's position.
All the enemy's guns were ranged against us from both sides.
The enemy's troops poured through an opening in our defenses.
Our soldiers fought all day to pierce through the enemy's defences.
With a shout of victory, he thrust his sword into his enemy's body.
Great dangers can result from misconceiving of the enemy's intentions.
It was the blockade of all the enemy's major ports that finally won the war.
The first man who stepped foot on the enemy's soil was doomed at once to die.
In those days you merely fingered the victim and in a few days your enemy's body was discovered in the gutter. *
